ce:section.ce:para:
The surface topographies of rGO electrode and rGO/NCDs electrode were characterised using SEM. In Fig. 1
                        a and 1b, the flexible fibrous CDI electrodes exhibited a homogeneous network structure formed by long flexuous filaments intertwined with each other. On the electrode surface, rGO sheets were presented as embedded, free and wrapped between adjacent fibers. Notably, the formation of a 'plane-to-linear' conductive network facilitated the transfer of electrons and provided abundant channels for the entry of solutions, which favored capacitive performance. The BET test results (Table 1
                        ) showed that the SSA, pore volume and average pore size of rGO/NCDs electrode were all enhanced compared to rGO electrode. This result indicated that the porous structure of the CDI electrode was improved, caused by the doped NCDs nanoparticles.
